never coming back. Never, ever, ever...

487
00:31:29,354 --> 00:31:32,721
-Come here. Come on.
-Leave me alone!

488
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:34,916
-No, sweetheart!
-SUNG LEE: Let me go!

489
00:31:34,993 --> 00:31:39,123
Sung Lee? What happened?
What happened? Sweetie, here.

490
00:31:39,197 --> 00:31:41,131
Come here. Tell me, what happened?

491
00:31:42,467 --> 00:31:43,866
JORDAN: What's wrong, Sung Lee?
What is it?

492
00:31:46,537 --> 00:31:48,767
-What happened?
-Kaleb told her about Mom and Dad.

493
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:50,373
(SUNG LEE SOBBING)

494
00:31:51,409 --> 00:31:54,845
I told her.
Mom and dad are not coming back.

495
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:11,418
JORDAN: (SOFTLY)
Sleepy time now, sleepy time.

496
00:32:34,218 --> 00:32:35,480
Asleep, finally.

497
00:32:36,154 --> 00:32:37,280
Hey, how was school?

498
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:39,615
American students are different.

499
00:32:40,325 --> 00:32:41,314
How's that?

500
00:32:42,427 --> 00:32:43,451
Just are.

501
00:32:45,063 --> 00:32:46,052
You don't like them?

502
00:32:46,831 --> 00:32:49,459
I like them, they're just not serious.

503
00:32:49,534 --> 00:32:52,128
-Some are, but mostly not.
-Jordan...

504
00:32:52,770 --> 00:32:56,399
Are you hungry?
You want a bowl of cereal or milk

505
00:32:56,474 --> 00:32:58,408
or you can... We can talk or...

506
00:32:58,509 --> 00:33:02,639
No, thanks, I'm just going to go to bed.
Good night.

507
00:33:04,415 --> 00:33:05,404
Good night.

508
00:33:08,853 --> 00:33:11,879
Oh, oh, oh, I'm coming around.
I'm coming around.

509
00:33:11,956 --> 00:33:13,287
Oh, oh!

510
00:33:14,692 --> 00:33:15,989
(JASON EXCLAIMS)

511
00:33:16,961 --> 00:33:18,622
You beat me again.

512
00:33:19,597 --> 00:33:21,758
Boys, it's time to go to bed.

513
00:33:23,101 --> 00:33:24,625
Come on, let's brush your teeth.

514
00:33:30,174 --> 00:33:32,574
(PATRIOTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

515
00:33:35,480 --> 00:33:38,313
(WHISPERING) Tell him what you did.
You must. Tell him.

516
00:33:38,883 --> 00:33:40,350
(STOPS MUSIC)

517
00:33:40,451 --> 00:33:41,782
Hey, boys?

518
00:33:43,454 --> 00:33:44,546
Boys?

519
00:33:50,661 --> 00:33:53,095
It was me who did it. Not Kaleb.

520
00:33:53,231 --> 00:33:55,062
If you have a punishment,
it should be for me only.

521
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,431
You can use my computer
whenever you want,

522
00:33:57,602 --> 00:34:00,298
but what do you have to do first?

523
00:34:01,172 --> 00:34:03,766
-Ask permission.
-That's exactly right.

524
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:05,304
Do we all understand that?

525
00:34:06,277 --> 00:34:08,006
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, Major Jason.

526
00:34:11,649 --> 00:34:13,241
Hey, are you asleep?

527
00:34:15,119 --> 00:34:16,780
Not even a little.

528
00:34:17,789 --> 00:34:19,689
Jason, I can't do this.

529
00:34:20,258 --> 00:34:22,192
Look, it's not forever.

530
00:34:25,329 --> 00:34:27,854
No, I mean I can't. Like...

531
00:34:28,032 --> 00:34:33,470
I don't have any parenting genes
or nurturing instincts or something.

532
00:34:33,538 --> 00:34:36,701
You know how to love.
That's just who you are.

533
00:34:37,408 --> 00:34:38,875
If that was all that it took.

534
00:34:41,145 --> 00:34:42,635
Listen, Jason.

535
00:34:43,014 --> 00:34:44,072
Hey.

536
00:34:44,715 --> 00:34:48,082
These kids are hurting
and they may not show it yet,

537
00:34:48,152 --> 00:34:51,417
but it's only a matter of time until,
I don't know,

538
00:34:52,156 --> 00:34:55,353
something terrible happens,
and then what do we do?

539
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:59,222
We're going to handle it, together.

540
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:37,630
LINDFORD:
You had it rough over there, I know.

541
00:35:39,036 --> 00:35:41,834
But you were born to fly.
You know that, too, don't you, son?

542
00:35:43,074 --> 00:35:46,305
-That was then, this is now, sir.
-You so sure about that?

543
00:35:46,477 --> 00:35:47,944
Yes, sir, I am.

544
00:35:48,012 --> 00:35:53,382
Let's put it to the test then,
shall we? Go on, have a pew.

545
00:35:57,355 --> 00:36:01,485
Jason, what if I was to tell you
I wanted you back in the cockpit?

546
00:36:02,894 --> 00:36:04,259
I gave it up for a reason, sir.

547
00:36:04,395 --> 00:36:08,855
As you said, "That was then,
this is now." The design team wants you.

548
00:36:09,700 --> 00:36:13,534
You can be your own test pilot.
The Air Force is looking at the F-35.

549
00:36:15,039 --> 00:36:16,802
The F-35 Lightning, that's a...

550
00:36:16,874 --> 00:36:19,934
-Outstanding jet fighter is what it is.
-Yes, it is.

551
00:36:20,011 --> 00:36:22,571
-And highly underestimated.
-Yes, it was.

552
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:28,683
It would mean a fair bit of travel,
longer stay-overs at Langley.

553
00:36:28,753 --> 00:36:30,103
Sally might take issues with it,

554
00:36:30,104 --> 00:36:33,281
but you can deploy countermeasures
for that, right?

555
00:36:33,424 --> 00:36:34,857
(SIGHS)

556
00:36:37,061 --> 00:36:38,619
Do I have time to consider, sir?

557
00:36:40,097 --> 00:36:44,625
All right, talk it over with Sally,
but get back to me pronto.

558
00:36:44,735 --> 00:36:48,227
By the way, saw Sally at the ceremony.
She's still quite the character.

559
00:36:48,372 --> 00:36:50,135
Yeah, she's all that, huh?

560
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:55,612
Hey, before you go, a few fellows
might want to shake your hand.

561
00:36:56,380 --> 00:36:57,369
Jenny.

562
00:37:00,384 --> 00:37:01,408
(LAUGHING)

563
00:37:01,485 --> 00:37:03,715
-Babba Everby.
-How are you, J?

564
00:37:04,322 --> 00:37:05,846
You speed maniac.

565
00:37:05,923 --> 00:37:08,687
Bagels, Westskape, Freddy.

566
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:13,156
Look at you, you city slicker.
You still driving that old Chevelle?

567
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:15,563
Of course I am.
You still doing the NASCAR thing?

568
00:37:15,633 --> 00:37:16,622
As much as I can.

569
00:37:16,701 --> 00:37:19,295
Not that we're trying to persuade you
or anything, Jason.

570
00:37:19,370 --> 00:37:21,304
No, no, I'd never suspect that.

571
00:37:21,372 --> 00:37:23,135
(LAUGHS)

572
00:37:23,207 --> 00:37:25,937
KLAY: They're looking for a replacement
for the West Coast leg of the tour

573
00:37:26,010 --> 00:37:28,604
-and you're the... There you go, Charlie.
-I'm what?

574
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:31,307
-Yeah, get down there, sweetie.
-Hello! Hi, I'm what?

575
00:37:31,382 --> 00:37:33,282
-Get down. Yes, yes.
-Excuse me, Klay.

576
00:37:33,351 --> 00:37:34,579
You're killing me. I'm what?

577
00:37:34,652 --> 00:37:36,176
And you're the one they want.

578
00:37:36,487 --> 00:37:37,852
(CHARLIE WHIMPERING)

579
00:37:37,922 --> 00:37:40,186
They're there with an offer,
so what do you want me to tell them?

580
00:37:40,258 --> 00:37:43,785
Look, I told you Milwaukee was great.
I'm ready for this, this is it.

581
00:37:44,028 --> 00:37:45,689
-Oh, yeah.
-Wow.

582
00:37:47,999 --> 00:37:49,193
Charlie.

583
00:37:49,433 --> 00:37:51,765
Now, really.

584
00:37:53,037 --> 00:37:54,265
Really.

585
00:37:54,472 --> 00:37:55,632
-Okay, then.
-Yeah.

586
00:37:55,706 --> 00:37:57,401
-I'll set up the meeting at Macambo.
-Great.

587
00:37:57,475 --> 00:37:58,874
You never know who is going to be there.

588
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:01,503
So you're saying
I should put my game face on.

589
00:38:01,579 --> 00:38:03,740
Yeah, yeah, that and do that
little "Sally thing" that you do, eh?

590
00:38:03,814 --> 00:38:04,838
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

591
00:38:04,915 --> 00:38:06,007
Okay. Hang on.

592
00:38:08,886 --> 00:38:13,050
Hello? Oh, no, is she okay?

593
00:38:14,225 --> 00:38:16,887
Yeah, no, I'm on my way.
I'm on my way. Thanks. Okay.

594
00:38:16,961 --> 00:38:19,191
-Hey, hey, Sally?
-Gotta go. Bye, Klay.

595
00:38:19,263 --> 00:38:20,423
-Sally, where are you going?
-(WHIMPERING)

596
00:38:25,736 --> 00:38:29,035
Oh, oh. I'm sorry, excuse me, could you
tell me where the nurse's office is?

597
00:38:29,373 --> 00:38:30,635
Thank you very much.

598
00:38:33,511 --> 00:38:36,139
-Excuse me, I'm Sally Danville. I...
-Yes.

599
00:38:36,247 --> 00:38:37,714
-What happened?
-Oh, it's all right, Mrs. Danville.

600
00:38:37,782 --> 00:38:40,182
-Yeah? Yeah, okay.
-She's fine. It's just an earache.

601
00:38:40,251 --> 00:38:41,980
-SALLY: What do I do?
-Some warm water,

602
00:38:42,053 --> 00:38:44,112
a couple of these drops every four hours.

603
00:38:44,188 --> 00:38:45,655
She should be better in the morning,
I'm sure.

604
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,728
Just a little bit of this...

605
00:39:00,204 --> 00:39:01,296
Okay.

606
00:39:03,574 --> 00:39:05,474
Want a little "tell me something"?

607
00:39:11,248 --> 00:39:12,340
Okay.

608
00:39:52,022 --> 00:39:53,649
(CLATTERING)

609
00:39:57,395 --> 00:39:58,657
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

610
00:39:58,896 --> 00:40:00,329
I'm sorry.

611
00:40:04,702 --> 00:40:08,160
-Hey, what's going on down here?
-KALEB: I'm sorry, Auntie Sally.

612
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:09,395
It's okay.

613
00:40:09,774 --> 00:40:12,675
I was not paying attention.
Can you forgive me?

614
00:40:13,010 --> 00:40:14,534
-Yeah.
-I'll speak to him.

615
00:40:14,645 --> 00:40:15,821
No, Jordan,

616
00:40:16,132 --> 00:40:17,978
-can you just let me this time...
-No, it should be me.

617
00:40:18,048 --> 00:40:22,348
No, my drums, my house, my turn.

618
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:23,444
Please?

619
00:40:23,521 --> 00:40:25,489
(SPEAKING FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

620
00:40:30,294 --> 00:40:32,023
I guess you like music, huh?

621
00:40:32,296 --> 00:40:35,788
-In my country, we have music every day.
-Wow, that's fun.

622
00:40:35,966 --> 00:40:37,263
I'm sorry I did that.

623
00:40:37,635 --> 00:40:40,866
Dude, it's fine.
You know what? Curiosity is good.

624
00:40:40,938 --> 00:40:44,374
Never lose it.
Let's just not worry about this, okay?

625
00:40:44,875 --> 00:40:48,367
How would you like to jam with my band?

626
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:49,640
-Can I really?
-Yeah.

627
00:40:49,713 --> 00:40:51,112
I think I can arrange it, yeah.

628
00:40:52,616 --> 00:40:54,049
I'm very ashamed.

629
00:40:56,253 --> 00:40:59,620
I told you,
it's not a big deal, seriously.

630
00:40:59,757 --> 00:41:04,888
I'm not ashamed about these drums. I'm
ashamed about what I said to my sister.

631
00:41:06,197 --> 00:41:07,596
(EXCLAIMS)

632
00:41:07,932 --> 00:41:09,627
Look, sit down.

633
00:41:11,602 --> 00:41:12,933
(SALLY SIGHS)

634
00:41:15,906 --> 00:41:19,069
Listen, Kaleb, I know
you weren't trying to hurt Sung Lee.

635
00:41:19,143 --> 00:41:20,872
You were just telling her the truth.

636
00:41:20,945 --> 00:41:24,779
Telling the truth
is a really hard thing to say.

637
00:41:26,450 --> 00:41:31,046
Actually, it takes a lot of courage,
which must mean you're pretty brave.

638
00:41:32,289 --> 00:41:34,154
It's nothing to be ashamed of, right?

639
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:37,385
All right?

640
00:41:38,128 --> 00:41:40,688
-Auntie Sally?
-Yeah?

641
00:41:41,866 --> 00:41:46,667
I love living here
with you and Major Jason.

642
00:42:12,830 --> 00:42:14,855
(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING ON HEADPHONES)

643
00:42:21,872 --> 00:42:23,601
Hi, beautiful girl.

644
00:42:26,477 --> 00:42:30,436
Sorry I'm late.
I ran into Bobby Everby at the base.

645
00:42:30,514 --> 00:42:32,175
Remember him from the squadron?

646
00:42:32,249 --> 00:42:34,513
Used to drive NASCAR
before he joined the service.

647
00:42:35,920 --> 00:42:37,217
-So you were at the base?
-Yeah.

648
00:42:37,288 --> 00:42:39,188
Met with General Lindford,
but I'll tell you about that later.

649
00:42:39,256 --> 00:42:42,020
-How was your day?
-Wonderful.

650
00:42:43,694 --> 00:42:47,152
-No. Not wonderful.
-Oh, it sounds complicated.

651
00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:52,328
Yeah, it would have been simpler
if you were here.

652
00:42:53,203 --> 00:42:55,171
All right, what happened?

653
00:42:57,441 --> 00:43:01,400
Details don't matter, really,
just kids are getting attached,

654
00:43:01,478 --> 00:43:06,506
and the time,
responsibility and our old lives,

655
00:43:06,584 --> 00:43:09,951
we're just not gonna really get them
back until we do something about it.

656
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:14,819
Did you talk to Dorothy? And?

657
00:43:18,696 --> 00:43:19,890
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

658
00:43:19,964 --> 00:43:21,329
DOROTHY: Thank you so much.

659
00:43:22,399 --> 00:43:23,388
Well?

660
00:43:23,601 --> 00:43:24,898
Well, well.

661
00:43:26,070 --> 00:43:27,970
SALLY: I don't know,
I just feel weird about it.

662
00:43:28,038 --> 00:43:29,232
JASON: Yeah.

663
00:43:29,306 --> 00:43:31,331
I mean, you're right,
it's the right thing to do,

664
00:43:31,408 --> 00:43:34,172
-and they're great people...
-Wonderful people.

665
00:43:34,244 --> 00:43:35,233
The best.

666
00:43:35,479 --> 00:43:36,810
So, what do you think?

667
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:38,313
What's not to like?

668
00:43:38,649 --> 00:43:40,947
-Would we still get to see them?
-That's not a problem,

669
00:43:41,018 --> 00:43:42,883
-just needs to be convenient.
-Right.

670
00:43:42,953 --> 00:43:45,012
So I will expedite the paperwork

671
00:43:45,089 --> 00:43:49,753
and Kaleb and Sung Lee
can probably move in this weekend.

672
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,393
-Excuse me?
-Say that again.

673
00:43:52,396 --> 00:43:53,385
Oh, no, don't worry.

674
00:43:53,464 --> 00:43:56,865
I have a very good family
willing to meet with Javier and Jordan.

675
00:43:56,934 --> 00:43:58,765
They're not right in town...

676
00:43:58,836 --> 00:44:01,999
Wait, wait a minute.
You're going to split them up?

677
00:44:02,953 --> 00:44:04,781
I explained that it's difficult

678
00:44:04,782 --> 00:44:07,175
to find a family
that's willing to take all four...

679
00:44:07,277 --> 00:44:10,872
Wait a second. This just can't happen.
They need to go to the same...

680
00:44:10,948 --> 00:44:12,677
They need to go to the same family.

681
00:44:12,750 --> 00:44:16,846
Mrs. Danville,
you were the one on the phone to me

682
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:20,583
about the children becoming attached
and how it was too painful

683
00:44:20,658 --> 00:44:23,320
-for you to deal with it...
-Look, I need this to happen the right way,

684
00:44:23,394 --> 00:44:25,157
and I just don't have time for this,
I just don't.

685
00:44:25,229 --> 00:44:27,459
-Sal.
-No, look, Jason,

686
00:44:27,531 --> 00:44:30,364
I have an opportunity to go on tour.
Do you know what that could mean?

687
00:44:30,434 --> 00:44:31,526
Why didn't you tell me?

688
00:44:31,702 --> 00:44:34,762
Cause everything is out of control.
You know, our lives,

689
00:44:34,838 --> 00:44:37,568
I'd really like them back
the way they used to be, you know?

690
00:44:37,641 --> 00:44:41,008
-Sally and I need to talk about this.
-I can see that.

691
00:44:42,413 --> 00:44:46,406
-What is this about a tour?
-Klay's got something lined up for me.

692
00:44:46,550 --> 00:44:47,915
JASON: Oh.

693
00:44:48,318 --> 00:44:50,479
-Don't act so excited for me.
-It's not that.

694
00:44:50,554 --> 00:44:51,543
-It's...
-What is it?

695
00:44:51,622 --> 00:44:54,750
It's just...
I told you I met with General Lindford.

696
00:44:54,825 --> 00:44:56,417
Yeah, no, I'm sorry.
I was a little out of it.

697
00:44:58,195 --> 00:44:59,753
He wants me to fly again.

698
00:45:01,865 --> 00:45:04,299
I thought you said
you'd never fly again.

699
00:45:04,868 --> 00:45:06,927
I can't turn this one down,
it's like a dream come true.

700
00:45:07,004 --> 00:45:08,335
-Great.
-(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

701
00:45:08,405 --> 00:45:10,270
So what you're saying is
that one of us needs to stay home

702
00:45:10,340 --> 00:45:11,671
-with these kids until...
-I'm not saying that.

703
00:45:11,742 --> 00:45:13,209
I'm just trying to put everything
on the table.

704
00:45:13,277 --> 00:45:15,404
Uh-huh, on the table, right.

705
00:45:15,479 --> 00:45:19,074
So both of us can see that your
practical opportunity beats my artsy...

706
00:45:19,149 --> 00:45:22,812
Hey, come on, that's not what I'm saying.
I mean...

707
00:45:22,886 --> 00:45:24,854
-What are you saying?
-Well... Let's... What...

708
00:45:24,922 --> 00:45:28,016
In terms of dollars,
that's true. It's true.

709
00:45:29,026 --> 00:45:31,494
What if there's a remote possibility
that I can actually make it?

710
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:33,154
Have you thought of that,
maybe I can actually make it?

711
00:45:33,230 --> 00:45:35,425
-Let's not get crazy here.
-For everything that I have done?

712
00:45:35,499 --> 00:45:37,399
No, I'm not getting crazy here.

713
00:45:37,468 --> 00:45:40,335
Listen, I'm just trying to figure out
how I'm supposed to live

714
00:45:40,404 --> 00:45:44,340
with a husband that I love,
this career that I have passion for

715
00:45:44,358 --> 00:45:48,208
and now these four kids that,
quite frankly, I feel responsible for.

716
00:45:53,450 --> 00:45:54,747
I just... Look...

717
00:45:55,819 --> 00:45:57,878
-I love you.
-I love you.

718
00:45:59,289 --> 00:46:02,816
-JAVIER: It's pronounced "Ugunda."
-Oh, Ugunda. Good to know.

719
00:46:03,293 --> 00:46:05,320
I doubt I'll make it there anytime soon.

720
00:46:05,366 --> 00:46:08,329
You should try. It's the
most beautiful country in Africa.

721
00:46:08,398 --> 00:46:11,026
-Sounds like you miss it, huh?
-I miss my friends.

722
00:46:11,101 --> 00:46:12,932
You know what? I have good news for you.

723
00:46:17,975 --> 00:46:20,603
Wow, look at this place.

724
00:46:22,079 --> 00:46:24,479
Who drives these cars? Students?

725
00:46:24,548 --> 00:46:26,038
(CAR ENGINE REVVING)

726
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:28,315
JAVIER: What kind of car is that?

727
00:46:33,690 --> 00:46:34,987
TAMBLYN: Pick it up, Jefferson.

728
00:46:36,935 --> 00:46:38,550
CHRISTINE: Coach Tamblyn!

729
00:46:38,939 --> 00:46:41,397
This is Javier Solarte.

730
00:46:41,502 --> 00:46:42,521
Ah!

731
00:46:42,550 --> 00:46:44,731
If it isn't the man
with the golden boot.

732
00:46:44,802 --> 00:46:47,032
Javier, good to meet you, son.

733
00:46:47,057 --> 00:46:49,347
I'm Tamblyn,
I'm the football coach here.

734
00:46:49,350 --> 00:46:51,071
I'm honored to meet you, sir.

735
00:46:51,141 --> 00:46:53,541
So, you played a bit of football, huh,
someplace else?

736
00:46:53,977 --> 00:46:55,342
Yes, sir. I like football.

737
00:46:55,412 --> 00:46:58,279
Like it, don't like it,
I don't really care,

738
00:46:58,348 --> 00:47:01,181
all I'm interested in is
are you any good at it?

739
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:04,246
Wychowski! Danny!

740
00:47:04,721 --> 00:47:07,246
Throw this man the ball.
Let's see what he can do with it.

741
00:47:07,524 --> 00:47:08,718
He's a football player.

742
00:47:11,295 --> 00:47:12,284
Go for it.

743
00:47:28,946 --> 00:47:34,642
Kind of European, but we can work
with it. He's got potential.

744
00:47:33,750 --> 00:47:35,240
(PLAYERS LAUGHING)

745
00:47:36,787 --> 00:47:39,119
BOY 1 : Where are you from?
BOY 2: What's he doing?

746
00:47:44,795 --> 00:47:45,819
Lighten up, son.

747
00:47:45,896 --> 00:47:48,228
-DANNY: Kid's a loser, Coach.
-Javier!

748
00:47:48,732 --> 00:47:49,858
-TAMBLYN: Back to work!
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)

749
00:47:50,167 --> 00:47:52,328
-You tricked me!
-I was doing you a favor.

750
00:47:52,402 --> 00:47:55,599
That? That was no favor.
That was to make me a fool!

751
00:47:55,672 --> 00:47:58,402
But you know what? I have been around!
I have been on the street!

752
00:47:58,475 --> 00:48:01,808
I am no fool.
I knew that ball was not a soccer ball.

753
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:05,310
Javier, trust me, you showed them
and they were impressed!

754
00:48:05,382 --> 00:48:06,679
They laughed!

755
00:48:06,750 --> 00:48:09,378
That's just guys, that's what they do.

756
00:48:10,387 --> 00:48:13,550
Hey, I'm sorry
if you thought that I tricked you.

757
00:48:14,491 --> 00:48:18,291
Look at me. Hey, Javier, look at me.

758
00:48:18,996 --> 00:48:20,896
I would never do that.

759
00:48:21,231 --> 00:48:25,190
Never, okay? Okay?

760
00:48:26,336 --> 00:48:28,201
Come on, let's get out of here.

761
00:48:40,217 --> 00:48:41,206
Hey, Jordan!

762
00:48:42,152 --> 00:48:43,141
Hello.

763
00:48:45,255 --> 00:48:46,279
Hey, where's Javier?

764
00:48:46,390 --> 00:48:49,188
Gone out with some girl with blue hair,
but said he'd be home for dinner.

765
00:48:51,728 --> 00:48:53,252
Oh, this is Noah.

766
00:48:53,330 --> 00:48:55,423
Noah Roorda. Hey, Mrs. Danville.
How's it going?

767
00:48:55,499 --> 00:48:57,194
Pretty well, Noah. Nice to meet you.

768
00:48:57,267 --> 00:48:59,497
You, too. Hey, I checked out your music.
It's pretty cool.

769
00:48:59,569 --> 00:49:01,059
I really like the acoustic stuff.

770
00:49:01,571 --> 00:49:03,061
-Thanks.
-Keep up the good work.

771
00:49:03,140 --> 00:49:04,334
-Yeah, you too.
-Bye.

772
00:49:05,776 --> 00:49:08,040
-Can we just go?
-Okay.

773
00:49:13,283 --> 00:49:14,978
He promised me he'd be here.
He never breaks a promise.

774
00:49:15,052 --> 00:49:17,213
-I'm going to kill him.
-It's not good to kill.

775
00:49:17,287 --> 00:49:19,812
-Thank you, Kaleb, I'll remember that.
-You'd better remember.

776
00:49:19,890 --> 00:49:21,357
All right. Hey, guys.

777
00:49:21,658 --> 00:49:23,785
Lighten up, take a breather.

778
00:49:25,529 --> 00:49:27,053
Bet you can't do this.

779
00:49:32,302 --> 00:49:33,792
Don't pretend
like you're not impressed there.

780
00:49:33,870 --> 00:49:34,996
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

781
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,302
Watch this.

782
00:49:42,212 --> 00:49:43,440
Hello?

783
00:49:45,582 --> 00:49:47,743
Okay, Javier.
All right, all right, just calm down.

784
00:49:47,818 --> 00:49:49,376
What... The police?

785
00:49:50,854 --> 00:49:54,722
Okay, tell them we're going to be
right there, okay? All right.

786
00:49:55,592 --> 00:49:56,581
What's the situation?

787
00:49:57,027 --> 00:49:58,085
Not good.

788
00:50:00,497 --> 00:50:01,828
SALLY: Jordan! Jordan! Jordan, wait.

789
00:50:01,898 --> 00:50:04,696
He's my brother,
I should be the one that goes. Why you?

790
00:50:04,768 --> 00:50:07,168
Because I need you to stay here
with Kaleb and Sung Lee.

791
00:50:07,237 --> 00:50:08,932
He's my family, not yours.

792
00:50:09,139 --> 00:50:11,073
SALLY: Javier is our responsibility.

793
00:50:12,676 --> 00:50:14,541
You think you know my brother
better than I do?

794
00:50:16,279 --> 00:50:18,509
Jordan, I didn't say that.

795
00:50:19,316 --> 00:50:22,513
What I am saying is that right now,
you're in charge of this house

796
00:50:22,586 --> 00:50:24,247
and two young children.

797
00:50:24,321 --> 00:50:27,119
I need you to do this for us, please.

798
00:50:45,242 --> 00:50:47,073
We're going to get through this.

799
00:50:47,477 --> 00:50:50,037
It'll all turn out, you'll see.

800
00:51:09,266 --> 00:51:12,758
-Hold it. Hold it.
-We're responsible for Javier Solarte.

801
00:51:12,836 --> 00:51:14,098
POLICEMAN:
It's all right, he's free to go.

802
00:51:14,171 --> 00:51:16,935
We just got to finish
a little paperwork, okay?

803
00:51:26,316 --> 00:51:30,548
Excuse me. Hey, I'm Christine.
I was with Javier.

804
00:51:30,620 --> 00:51:33,054
All those guys say Javier started it,
but he didn't.

805
00:51:33,123 --> 00:51:34,954
They teased him about playing football.

806
00:51:35,425 --> 00:51:37,691
They're just jealous 'cause
he has way more talent than them,

807
00:51:37,716 --> 00:51:39,163
especially Danny.

808
00:51:39,863 --> 00:51:41,524
-Who's Danny?
-CHRISTINE: Quarterback.

809
00:51:41,598 --> 00:51:45,090
He's totally insecure because
the coach is so impressed with Javier.

810
00:51:45,168 --> 00:51:46,635
JASON: What, the football coach?

811
00:51:46,703 --> 00:51:48,534
Oh, yeah, he really wants Javier
to play on the team.

812
00:51:48,872 --> 00:51:51,397
-I would never do that.
-Hey, never say never.

813
00:51:51,741 --> 00:51:54,369
-Understand what I'm saying?
-Yes, sir.

814
00:51:54,644 --> 00:51:56,168
I want you to get in the car.

815
00:51:56,780 --> 00:51:57,872
Thanks.

816
00:52:05,322 --> 00:52:06,311
JORDAN: What happened?

817
00:52:06,490 --> 00:52:08,321
Everything is okay,
it's nothing serious.

818
00:52:08,425 --> 00:52:10,188
-Are you hurt?
-It's not mine.

819
00:52:10,260 --> 00:52:11,454
(SIGHS)

820
00:52:12,963 --> 00:52:13,952
Take it off. I'll wash it.

821
00:52:14,030 --> 00:52:16,692
-Jordan, you don't have to...
-I want to! That okay with you?

822
00:52:27,043 --> 00:52:29,773
Hey, hey, look at this.
Let me show you something.

823
00:52:29,846 --> 00:52:33,942
Look. Jordan Solarte, date of birth.
Sixteen, sweet 16.

824
00:52:34,017 --> 00:52:35,279
This is a huge deal.

825
00:52:35,352 --> 00:52:37,980
I'm going to throw her a party
and you know what?

826
00:52:38,054 --> 00:52:41,717
I'm going to win this girl's heart if
I have to jump out of her cake to do it.

827
00:52:44,961 --> 00:52:47,259
So what I want to know is
are you going to be there for it

828
00:52:47,330 --> 00:52:50,493
or are you going to be
in the service again flying jets?

829
00:52:51,568 --> 00:52:55,265
Look, if I take this job,
I'm not gonna be traveling all the time,

830
00:52:55,772 --> 00:52:58,832
and if I am, I'll be back
on the weekends to make up for it.

831
00:52:59,242 --> 00:53:03,338
Weekends, nice.
So, I'll just put my life on hold.

832
00:53:06,716 --> 00:53:09,207
Sal, it's going to work out.

833
00:53:09,286 --> 00:53:11,447
Dorothy is going to find a family
for these kids

834
00:53:11,521 --> 00:53:14,513
and we're gonna get
back on with our lives, okay?

835
00:53:19,963 --> 00:53:21,260
Look, you know,

836
00:53:21,731 --> 00:53:23,392
I don't know much about
this parenting thing,

837
00:53:23,466 --> 00:53:25,093
but I know these kids,

838
00:53:25,168 --> 00:53:30,299
and kids need a male role model
or a father figure.

839
00:53:30,507 --> 00:53:32,168
Especially those two boys, they...

840
00:53:32,776 --> 00:53:36,041
They need to see how to be a man,
how to do man stuff.

841
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:38,378
Like, right now.

842
00:53:38,448 --> 00:53:40,575
-Okay. Okay.
-Okay what?

843
00:53:42,919 --> 00:53:44,216
Man stuff it is.

844
00:53:46,056 --> 00:53:48,183
(FEELS LIKE TONIGHT PLAYING)

845
00:54:02,439 --> 00:54:04,964
-Hey, Babba.
-Hey, city slicker.

846
00:54:07,377 --> 00:54:09,902
Jeff. Guys, this is Jeff Burton.

847
00:54:10,013 --> 00:54:12,311
-Here's some friends I want you to meet.
-Hi.

848
00:54:12,382 --> 00:54:14,282
-How we doing?
-All right, and you?

849
00:54:14,351 --> 00:54:15,909
-Good to see you.
-You must be Jason Danville.

850
00:54:15,986 --> 00:54:17,385
-How are you?
-Nice meeting you.

851
00:54:17,454 --> 00:54:18,478
Nice to meet you guys.

852
00:54:18,555 --> 00:54:21,991
Hey, guys, this guy's the real deal.
He drives racecars.

853
00:54:22,192 --> 00:54:24,353
I'm a dad, too,
so I'm pretty happy about that.

854
00:54:24,427 --> 00:54:26,258
He took first place 21 times.

855
00:54:26,329 --> 00:54:28,263
Hey, man, you know,
I've been lucky, all right.

856
00:54:28,331 --> 00:54:30,356
-BOBBY: Thank you.
-Hey, junior.

857
00:54:30,634 --> 00:54:31,794
Here are some hats.

858
00:54:31,868 --> 00:54:33,460
Here you go, fellows,
hope you have a great time.

859
00:54:33,536 --> 00:54:34,560
-Thank you.
-Nice meeting you.

860
00:54:34,638 --> 00:54:36,003
Have a good time. I'll see you.

861
00:54:36,072 --> 00:54:37,096
All right.

862
00:55:11,675 --> 00:55:14,667
SALLY: Hello, I'm looking for a cake.

863
00:55:15,045 --> 00:55:19,072
Something like, you know,
kind of a big, big rectangle, this tall.

864
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:20,138
Something like that?

865
00:55:20,984 --> 00:55:22,576
Cool. Thank you.

866
00:55:22,719 --> 00:55:25,654
WOMAN: (OVER PA) Attention shoppers,
the store will be closing shortly.

867
00:55:25,722 --> 00:55:27,314
Please take your items to the cashier.

868
00:55:27,390 --> 00:55:29,585
Get some streamers, maybe some balloons.

869
00:55:38,868 --> 00:55:40,802
Hey, it's a zebra, huh?

870
00:55:42,339 --> 00:55:46,435
BOTH: (SINGING)
Zebra, zebra, please get better

871
00:55:46,710 --> 00:55:50,510
Zebra, zebra, you're okay

872
00:55:57,687 --> 00:56:01,919
When I was a little girl,
I had to write a paper in school

873
00:56:01,991 --> 00:56:06,485
about an imaginary character
named Roxy the Midnight Hairdresser.

874
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:09,028
And in your sleep,
she comes to visit you,

875
00:56:09,232 --> 00:56:11,962
and she lands on your head
and she does a little dance.

876
00:56:12,035 --> 00:56:14,902
When you wake up,
you have a fancy little hairdo.

877
00:56:15,105 --> 00:56:16,129
(CHUCKLES)

878
00:56:16,206 --> 00:56:20,040
You like that?
Okay, you ready to go to sleep?

879
00:56:20,910 --> 00:56:22,002
Okay.

880
00:56:24,647 --> 00:56:25,705
Zebra, too.

881
00:56:29,052 --> 00:56:30,110
No!

882
00:56:31,654 --> 00:56:32,746
Cheater.

883
00:56:35,392 --> 00:56:36,950
You don't play as well as you think.

884
00:56:39,229 --> 00:56:41,459
You're going to be sorry
you even thought that.

885
00:56:42,065 --> 00:56:46,365
Offense, the essence of air power.

886
00:56:46,569 --> 00:56:52,371
A stupid cow leads her calf near the road.

887
00:56:54,444 --> 00:56:58,574
Peace through strength,
victory through devastation.

888
00:57:04,954 --> 00:57:06,251
(LAUGHS GLEEFULLY)

889
00:57:06,322 --> 00:57:12,318
The frog never hops in daylight for nothing.

890
00:57:13,730 --> 00:57:15,061
(EXCLAIMS)

891
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:16,289
What does that mean?

892
00:57:16,366 --> 00:57:17,355
No idea.

893
00:57:19,402 --> 00:57:23,498
All right.
Okay, you maybe played once or twice.

894
00:57:24,941 --> 00:57:27,375
Every night with my dad.

895
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:32,881
He was really good and way faster than me.

896
00:57:34,150 --> 00:57:35,879
What else did you do with him?

897
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:41,656
You know, (EXHALES) stuff.

898
00:57:42,225 --> 00:57:44,250
What kind of (EXHALES) stuff?

899
00:57:46,663 --> 00:57:48,392
We used to hike a lot.

900
00:57:49,899 --> 00:57:52,094
He'd show me different plants and...

901
00:57:54,103 --> 00:57:56,071
He taught me about all kinds of things.

902
00:57:56,506 --> 00:57:57,905
For example?

903
00:57:59,943 --> 00:58:03,845
Like the right way
to eat seasonal grasshoppers

904
00:58:04,914 --> 00:58:09,851
or how to ride a donkey backwards
by pricking its tail with a thorn.

905
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:19,788
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

906
00:58:19,896 --> 00:58:24,697
Sounds like he was a wonderful man. He
must have been a great father, I'm sure.

907
00:58:27,337 --> 00:58:28,326
He was.

908
00:58:32,642 --> 00:58:33,700
Good night.

909
00:58:34,177 --> 00:58:35,201
Good night, Jordan.

910
00:58:43,786 --> 00:58:44,775
(DOOR BELL RINGING)

911
00:58:48,992 --> 00:58:51,586
Hi, come on in.

912
00:58:51,928 --> 00:58:53,122
Sorry to come so early.

913
00:58:53,196 --> 00:58:55,255
-Hello, Dorothy.
-Hi.

914
00:58:55,598 --> 00:58:57,725
What I have to say can't wait.
Where are the children?

915
00:58:57,800 --> 00:58:59,028
They're having breakfast.

916
00:58:59,302 --> 00:59:00,530
I'll be quick about this.

917
00:59:01,237 --> 00:59:04,604
-About what?
-Family Services has stringent guidelines

918
00:59:04,674 --> 00:59:06,301
on guardianship and foster care.

919
00:59:06,376 --> 00:59:08,571
We take our responsibilities very seriously.

920
00:59:08,645 --> 00:59:09,634
Yeah, we know that.

921
00:59:10,680 --> 00:59:14,081
You said parenting wasn't in your
playbook, and clearly you were right.

922
00:59:16,052 --> 00:59:19,021
I just finished reading a police report
on Javier fighting.

923
00:59:20,089 --> 00:59:21,351
Another incident like that

924
00:59:21,424 --> 00:59:24,222
and the agency will remove
the children from your custody.

925
00:59:26,763 --> 00:59:29,698
Sorry to come so early,
but it had to be said.

926
00:59:38,908 --> 00:59:40,170
Don't listen to her.

927
00:59:40,243 --> 00:59:41,505
(SALLY EXHALES)

928
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:42,977
We're doing fine.

929
00:59:43,713 --> 00:59:44,702
Are we?

930
01:00:01,564 --> 01:00:03,896
-Coach.
-Pleased to meet you.

931
01:00:06,169 --> 01:00:07,363
Welcome back.

932
01:00:08,738 --> 01:00:10,672
Danny, come on in here.

933
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:16,143
Do a little peacemaking. Shake his hand.

934
01:00:19,682 --> 01:00:21,946
Tasey, get on in there.

935
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:28,420
Javier, these are your colors.
Wear them with pride.

936
01:00:29,158 --> 01:00:30,318
(DRUMS PLAYING)

937
01:00:35,565 --> 01:00:36,998
So, you're into music, eh, Kaleb?

938
01:00:37,166 --> 01:00:38,531
I like to play on the drum.

939
01:00:38,601 --> 01:00:42,162
My teacher told me the sound
of the drum is like the beating heart.

940
01:00:42,505 --> 01:00:45,906
But for me, with this sound,
I can forget all the bad things

941
01:00:45,975 --> 01:00:47,237
that happened in the past.

942
01:00:47,777 --> 01:00:50,371
Dude, that's my kind of music.

943
01:00:51,648 --> 01:00:56,142
I was thinking we'd start on the A to G.

944
01:00:56,219 --> 01:00:58,949
Think, you know, Stevie. Ready?
Let's hit it.

945
01:00:59,088 --> 01:01:01,181
One, two, three! Whoo!

946
01:01:01,257 --> 01:01:03,122
(PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC)

947
01:01:15,672 --> 01:01:16,866
Faster.

948
01:01:16,939 --> 01:01:18,304
(PLAYING FASTER)

949
01:01:25,181 --> 01:01:26,614
That's my guy.

950
01:01:29,752 --> 01:01:31,617
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

951
01:01:37,960 --> 01:01:39,120
No, thank you.

952
01:01:40,263 --> 01:01:44,757
-Look, see, that's from China.
-Oh, it sure is. It's beautiful.

953
01:01:45,568 --> 01:01:48,162
Should we skip? Skip, skip, skip.

954
01:01:53,309 --> 01:01:54,867
Thanks, thank you.

955
01:01:54,944 --> 01:01:57,913
-Kids? You brought kids?
-Yeah. This is Sung Lee and Kaleb...

956
01:01:57,980 --> 01:02:00,972
That's real nice. Now listen, sweetie,
you can't bring kids in here.

957
01:02:01,050 --> 01:02:03,314
Relax, Klay, it's just a sound check.

958
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:05,320
-Anyway, the joint's closed.
-It's all good, man.

959
01:02:05,388 --> 01:02:08,619
-Exactly.
-No, it's not good, it's not all good.

960
01:02:08,691 --> 01:02:11,125
Guess who's here.
Izzy Popyk, that's right.

961
01:02:11,194 --> 01:02:13,526
Cover of Billboard,
managed Fillmore West before he...

962
01:02:13,596 --> 01:02:16,895
-Klay, Klay, I know.
-Izzy Popyk's one big dude.

963
01:02:16,966 --> 01:02:18,126
Hello.

964
01:02:18,267 --> 01:02:20,997
Listen,
just take the kids up to the band room.

965
01:02:21,070 --> 01:02:23,664
-They won't make a sound, right? Right?
-Mmm-hmm.

966
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:25,405
KLAY: All right, that was sweet.
Let's go.

967
01:02:25,475 --> 01:02:28,410
-All right, all right, you guys, let's do this.
-Let's do it.

968
01:02:29,011 --> 01:02:31,172
Here you go.
Now, you all heard what Sally said.

969
01:02:31,247 --> 01:02:32,976
What Sally says is law, right?

970
01:02:33,049 --> 01:02:35,449
So I want you both to sit your butt...
Sit down here

971
01:02:35,518 --> 01:02:36,674
on this fine comfortable couch,

972
01:02:36,686 --> 01:02:38,885
don't move, don't make a sound
or nothing, right?

973
01:02:39,756 --> 01:02:42,054
Nod your heads
so I know you understand, then.

974
01:02:42,525 --> 01:02:43,549
All right, brilliant.

975
01:02:48,998 --> 01:02:50,260
-Look at this.
-Nice.

976
01:02:50,333 --> 01:02:55,532
Yo! You, effects kid.
Kill the smoke. It's a sound check!

977
01:02:56,706 --> 01:02:58,469
-(GUITAR BEING TUNED)
-That's him, that's Izzy.

978
01:03:07,950 --> 01:03:13,047
MAN 1 : Check.
Testing, check, testing, check 1, 2...

979
01:03:13,322 --> 01:03:16,018
MAN 2: You're actually going to do this?
Or you're going to do this.

980
01:03:16,359 --> 01:03:18,293
MAN 3: We've got about 15 minutes,
right just test this...

981
01:03:18,361 --> 01:03:20,192
-See if you're going to get this movement.
-MAN 1 : Check, check...

982
01:03:20,263 --> 01:03:22,026
WOMAN: Okay let's do a sound check.
Can we do a sound check anyone?

983
01:03:22,098 --> 01:03:24,066
(SOFTLY) Sung Lee. Sung Lee.

984
01:03:27,069 --> 01:03:28,559
-We're up next.
-All right.

985
01:03:28,638 --> 01:03:30,128
Okay. Yeah, I'm ready.

986
01:03:30,206 --> 01:03:32,902
Listen, just give Izzy a little taste,
all right? Just a wee bit.

987
01:03:33,109 --> 01:03:34,133
So this is an audition?

988
01:03:34,210 --> 01:03:36,838
No, no, no, you got the gig,
it's just he's a promoter

989
01:03:36,913 --> 01:03:38,676
with a ton of clout so, you know.

990
01:03:50,693 --> 01:03:53,594
-And who's this?
-This is Noah.

991
01:03:53,663 --> 01:03:56,257
Noah Roorda.
It's nice meeting you, Mr. Danville.

992
01:03:56,332 --> 01:03:58,300
-So you're Noah, huh?
-Yup.

993
01:03:58,401 --> 01:04:01,415
Javier, get your distance.
Three back and one.

994
01:04:02,169 --> 01:04:03,292
Danny?

995
01:04:07,276 --> 01:04:08,334
Let's see if you got it.

996
01:04:08,511 --> 01:04:09,603
Watch me.

997
01:04:09,979 --> 01:04:11,037
Hut!

998
01:04:18,054 --> 01:04:19,214
(EXCLAIMS)

999
01:04:19,589 --> 01:04:20,715
JORDAN: He did it! He did it!

1000
01:04:22,225 --> 01:04:24,955
That's my brother. He's the best.

1001
01:04:29,365 --> 01:04:30,354
Nice job, man.

1002
01:04:36,172 --> 01:04:37,696
-Where is Sally?
-(KALEB SHUSHING)

1003
01:04:40,409 --> 01:04:42,036
-Where is Sally?
-(SHUSHING)

1004
01:04:46,082 --> 01:04:49,313
MAN 1 : Everyone, hold on.
IZZY: Hold on there.

1005
01:04:52,188 --> 01:04:53,553
Those belong to you?

1006
01:04:55,258 --> 01:04:56,384
SALLY: Uh...

1007
01:04:59,195 --> 01:05:02,221
Yeah. Yeah, they do.

1008
01:05:02,832 --> 01:05:05,665
I don't ever allow kids in any venue
on tour, including this one.

1009
01:05:06,769 --> 01:05:08,964
Excuse me, is this place
even open right now?

1010
01:05:09,405 --> 01:05:11,999
Oh, that's not the point.
My tour, my rules.

1011
01:05:12,074 --> 01:05:15,134
So get them out of here right now
or you don't go on that stage.

1012
01:05:15,211 --> 01:05:17,771
You know what, Sally? Why don't
I just take them out for an ice cream?

1013
01:05:17,847 --> 01:05:18,871
You know, chocolate, vanilla...

1014
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:20,879
Klay, just leave it.

1015
01:05:22,551 --> 01:05:25,782
Yeah, you know what?
I've got this other gig.

1016
01:05:25,855 --> 01:05:30,986
It's actually a much bigger deal
at the moment, so...

1017
01:05:31,060 --> 01:05:32,891
DENNIS: What are you talking about?
SALLY: Hey, kids. Let's go.

1018
01:05:32,962 --> 01:05:36,261
We've put so much hard work into this...
If you go now, it's done!

1019
01:05:36,332 --> 01:05:37,424
Why are you doing this?

1020
01:05:37,700 --> 01:05:39,600
Change of plans, I'm outta here.

1021
01:05:45,708 --> 01:05:47,403
Perfect. Hey, you two,
how's that going over there?

1022
01:05:47,476 --> 01:05:48,465
We got it.

1023
01:05:48,544 --> 01:05:50,876
Auntie Sally, you want to see
what my sister and me learned at school?

1024
01:05:50,947 --> 01:05:52,073
Yeah.

1025
01:05:55,284 --> 01:05:57,548
Wow, that's awesome.
How about... My turn. Okay.

1026
01:05:57,620 --> 01:05:59,281
Guys, guys, they're here.
Hurry up, hide!

1027
01:06:06,896 --> 01:06:09,922
I don't know, something.
What's with the cloth?

1028
01:06:10,132 --> 01:06:11,121
Surprise!

1029
01:06:12,134 --> 01:06:14,034
ALL: Surprise!

1030
01:06:14,403 --> 01:06:16,371
Happy birthday!

1031
01:06:20,910 --> 01:06:22,070
What's wrong?

1032
01:06:23,779 --> 01:06:25,906
Nothing. This is... This is great.

1033
01:06:27,483 --> 01:06:29,508
You just shouldn't have
gone to all this trouble.

1034
01:06:29,585 --> 01:06:31,780
It wasn't trouble, it was fun.

1035
01:06:32,088 --> 01:06:33,282
(SUNG LEE CHUCKLING)

1036
01:06:35,257 --> 01:06:36,918
Wow. I mean, look at all of this.

1037
01:06:40,229 --> 01:06:43,164
I'm just going to go put my bag away.
Excuse me.

1038
01:06:49,271 --> 01:06:50,704
(KNOCKING AT DOOR)

1039
01:06:54,877 --> 01:06:56,845
-Hey.
-I don't want to talk about it.

1040
01:06:57,713 --> 01:06:58,771
Can I come in?

1041
01:07:03,452 --> 01:07:04,441
Jordan...

1042
01:07:07,757 --> 01:07:09,019
What's wrong?

1043
01:07:16,432 --> 01:07:17,865
Why did you have a party?

1044
01:07:21,270 --> 01:07:23,568
You turned 16. It's a big deal.

1045
01:07:24,507 --> 01:07:26,498
You know,
I thought it was a special occasion.

1046
01:07:31,147 --> 01:07:33,172
-It's not anymore.
-Jordan,

1047
01:07:34,683 --> 01:07:36,082
I'm sorry if I upset you.

1048
01:07:40,856 --> 01:07:42,187
I don't understand, though.

1049
01:07:42,491 --> 01:07:45,460
-It doesn't matter.
-Yeah, it matters.

1050
01:07:47,696 --> 01:07:49,163
It matters to me.

1051
01:07:52,835 --> 01:07:56,862
-Is it about your parents?
-Yeah.

1052
01:07:59,275 --> 01:08:00,503
You can tell me.

1053
01:08:00,910 --> 01:08:02,002
Can I?

1054
01:08:11,420 --> 01:08:12,614
Can I really?

1055
01:08:19,161 --> 01:08:20,253
You can.

1056
01:08:26,702 --> 01:08:31,730
My mom and I, we had this plan.

1057
01:08:34,743 --> 01:08:40,375
You know, we were together a lot because
we all helped them out in the villages

1058
01:08:41,917 --> 01:08:46,513
and we delivered food and medicine

1059
01:08:46,589 --> 01:08:51,390
and Mom and I never had any time together.

1060
01:08:54,029 --> 01:08:55,496
So, that's what we planned.

1061
01:08:57,299 --> 01:09:00,291
I told her what I really wanted
when I turned 16,

1062
01:09:01,437 --> 01:09:03,905
what I wanted more than anything
was just one day,

1063
01:09:05,841 --> 01:09:08,036
just one day just the two of us.

1064
01:09:11,380 --> 01:09:14,008
No party, just...

1065
01:09:15,651 --> 01:09:19,815
...time together, but...

1066
01:09:22,925 --> 01:09:24,790
No wonder you didn't want a party.

1067
01:09:28,631 --> 01:09:30,622
I didn't even want a birthday.

1068
01:09:33,302 --> 01:09:35,236
I want my mom and dad back.

1069
01:09:38,541 --> 01:09:40,065
(SOBBING)

1070
01:09:52,154 --> 01:09:53,712
Thanks for trusting me.

1071
01:09:56,992 --> 01:09:59,256
Thank you for being here for us.

1072
01:10:05,668 --> 01:10:06,760
What?

1073
01:10:06,835 --> 01:10:09,303
You should have seen Javier
kick that football today.

1074
01:10:09,905 --> 01:10:11,429
-Kid is incredible.
-Yeah.

1075
01:10:11,507 --> 01:10:13,407
I mean, you know, he's really incredible.

1076
01:10:15,811 --> 01:10:19,611
Oh. Jordan can ride a donkey backwards.

1077
01:10:19,682 --> 01:10:20,944
(LAUGHS)

1078
01:10:21,283 --> 01:10:22,773
There's a skill set, huh?

1079
01:10:23,652 --> 01:10:24,983
I'm not surprised.

1080
01:10:32,761 --> 01:10:33,921
Jason.

1081
01:10:34,630 --> 01:10:35,722
Hmm?

1082
01:10:36,732 --> 01:10:37,994
I've been thinking.

1083
01:10:39,635 --> 01:10:40,727
Yeah, me too.

1084
01:10:43,639 --> 01:10:46,870
I don't know, there's just
something about all this that

1085
01:10:48,944 --> 01:10:52,471
I honestly didn't expect,
but these kids...

1086
01:10:56,252 --> 01:10:57,617
Mmm.

1087
01:11:01,390 --> 01:11:02,584
You know what I mean?

1088
01:11:23,379 --> 01:11:24,471
Oh.

1089
01:11:27,149 --> 01:11:28,138
I... I...

1090
01:11:28,751 --> 01:11:31,117
-I know. It's not...
-It's not what we planned.

1091
01:11:31,253 --> 01:11:33,050
No, not in our planning, not at all,

1092
01:11:33,122 --> 01:11:35,147
-not a little bit.
-Not a little bit, but...

1093
01:11:36,358 --> 01:11:37,882
-Even so...
-Even so...

1094
01:11:41,997 --> 01:11:43,828
I know that it's going to take a lot of...

1095
01:11:44,066 --> 01:11:45,328
-Sacrifice.
-Sacrifice.

1096
01:11:45,434 --> 01:11:47,334
-Yeah, for both of us.
-I know.

1097
01:11:49,972 --> 01:11:51,234
But I think it's worth it.

1098
01:11:54,910 --> 01:11:56,138
I mean, do you think...

1099
01:11:59,348 --> 01:12:01,873
-Yes.
-Yeah? You think we can do this?

1100
01:12:04,987 --> 01:12:06,386
I'll call Dorothy.

1101
01:12:10,259 --> 01:12:11,556
Welcome to parenthood.

1102
01:12:11,627 --> 01:12:13,026
(LAUGHING)

1103
01:12:14,630 --> 01:12:16,325
-The final frontier.
-Hmm.

1104
01:12:16,932 --> 01:12:19,162
-What are we thinking?
-I don't know.

1105
01:12:43,058 --> 01:12:44,116
Hmm.

1106
01:12:46,028 --> 01:12:47,996
Klay. Hey, hi.

1107
01:12:49,098 --> 01:12:50,224
-Hey.
-How are you doing, Sal?

1108
01:12:50,299 --> 01:12:52,290
-Can I talk to you about something?
-Sure.

1109
01:12:52,368 --> 01:12:54,962
I've got some great new material.

1110
01:12:55,037 --> 01:12:56,561
Oh, that's great, so glad to hear that.

1111
01:12:56,638 --> 01:12:59,300
No, no, no, I need a big stage.

1112
01:12:59,641 --> 01:13:01,666
You know, bigger than anything
that I've done.

1113
01:13:01,744 --> 01:13:04,144
-Good luck with that.
-Listen, Klay.

1114
01:13:05,948 --> 01:13:08,246
-What do you want from me?
-I'm sorry.

1115
01:13:08,484 --> 01:13:11,647
-You messed up.
-I let you down, okay? I'm sorry.

1116
01:13:12,488 --> 01:13:14,388
-Please, Klay.
-What is it?

1117
01:13:20,229 --> 01:13:23,460
You're the only one that can
make this happen for me. Please?

1118
01:13:26,468 --> 01:13:28,197
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

1119
01:13:37,146 --> 01:13:38,579
Hello.

1120
01:13:45,421 --> 01:13:46,581
(BEEPS)

1121
01:13:47,423 --> 01:13:49,721
AUTOMATED VOICE:
You have one new message.

1122
01:13:51,560 --> 01:13:54,825
DOROTHY: Mr. and Mrs. Danville, good
news. We've found the perfect family

1123
01:13:54,930 --> 01:13:59,424
that will take all four children.
Transition is set for this weekend.

1124
01:14:11,580 --> 01:14:14,777
I need to come over now, Christine.
I gotta talk to you.

1125
01:14:18,487 --> 01:14:19,476
Gotta go.

1126
01:14:25,360 --> 01:14:27,885
AUTOMATED VOICE:
You have no new messages.

1127
01:15:00,496 --> 01:15:02,088
You know, in Dayton, Ohio,
two amazing facts,

1128
01:15:02,164 --> 01:15:05,190
the Wright brothers invented the very
first successful engine-powered aircraft,

1129
01:15:05,267 --> 01:15:06,632
and the first recording of Hang on Sloopy,

1130
01:15:06,702 --> 01:15:09,603
which became the first official
rock song of the State of Ohio.

1131
01:15:09,671 --> 01:15:12,469
-Do I appear nervous to you?
-(CHUCKLING) No.

1132
01:15:12,541 --> 01:15:14,202
-Not at all.
-No?

1133
01:15:15,110 --> 01:15:17,670
Oh. There's your... Everybody.

1134
01:15:24,786 --> 01:15:26,686
-NOAH: Kaleb.
-Hello, Noah.

1135
01:15:26,755 --> 01:15:27,881
NOAH: Hey, Mrs. Danville.

1136
01:15:27,956 --> 01:15:30,447
Hey, Noah. It's getting a little late,
don't you think?

1137
01:15:30,559 --> 01:15:31,787
Yeah, I'm just on my way home.

1138
01:15:37,032 --> 01:15:38,522
(WHISPERING)
Are you going to kiss my sister?

1139
01:15:39,067 --> 01:15:40,227
NOAH: (WHISPERING)
I'm not sure about that.

1140
01:15:40,636 --> 01:15:42,467
-Are you scared?
-Pretty much, yeah.

1141
01:15:42,771 --> 01:15:43,965
(SUNG LEE GIGGLING)

1142
01:15:45,908 --> 01:15:46,966
Good night.

1143
01:15:48,911 --> 01:15:50,003
Good night.

1144
01:15:52,381 --> 01:15:53,575
Oh.

1145
01:15:55,617 --> 01:15:57,084
(LAUGHING)

1146
01:15:59,087 --> 01:16:00,384
(EXHALES)

1147
01:16:01,390 --> 01:16:04,359
Wow, what a day.

1148
01:16:06,061 --> 01:16:07,153
Did you talk to Dorothy?

1149
01:16:07,362 --> 01:16:11,162
I left a message at the office
and they said that she'd call back.

1150
01:16:12,367 --> 01:16:14,164
You still okay with what we're doing?

1151
01:16:14,469 --> 01:16:17,461
Absolutely. What about you?

1152
01:16:18,073 --> 01:16:20,337
You okay with compromising
your dream come true?

1153
01:16:21,777 --> 01:16:25,372
(SIGHING) Well, you know,
I was thinking, after Buster crashed,

1154
01:16:26,648 --> 01:16:28,673
I had to go out there
and make a living for us.

1155
01:16:29,551 --> 01:16:34,011
That's still what I want to do.
It's just a bigger us, better dream.

1156
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:36,484
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1157
01:16:36,959 --> 01:16:38,426
Auntie Sally, Major Jason.

1158
01:16:38,493 --> 01:16:40,893
Javier is not in the house.
I looked everywhere.

1159
01:16:43,332 --> 01:16:46,165
-Anything?
-No, nothing.

1160
01:16:48,136 --> 01:16:49,228
(SIGHS)

1161
01:16:50,238 --> 01:16:52,069
-I'll go check out back.
-Hold on.

1162
01:16:54,610 --> 01:16:57,135
We've put out an APB.
It's just a matter of time.

1163
01:16:57,212 --> 01:16:58,770
Good, thank you.

1164
01:16:59,114 --> 01:17:00,877
You did the right thing coming in here.

1165
01:17:00,949 --> 01:17:02,416
I wish most parents had your common sense.

1166
01:17:04,319 --> 01:17:05,308
JASON: Thanks.

1167
01:17:07,522 --> 01:17:09,649
Yeah, he's at the Wells. They found him.

1168
01:17:12,694 --> 01:17:15,891
They found him
at the Malcolm Wells Hospital, Emergency.

1169
01:17:20,702 --> 01:17:23,694
JASON: We're here to see Javier Solarte.
NURSE: Are you family?

1170
01:17:24,172 --> 01:17:26,106
SALLY: Yeah, we are.
JASON: In a matter of speaking...

1171
01:17:26,174 --> 01:17:27,198
SALLY: We're responsible.

1172
01:17:27,275 --> 01:17:30,267
Hey, can I talk to you guys for a second?

1173
01:17:30,712 --> 01:17:32,976
-How's he doing? What's going on?
-No, no, he's okay.

1174
01:17:33,048 --> 01:17:35,107
-A few cuts, nothing broken. But...
-SALLY: Good.

1175
01:17:35,183 --> 01:17:38,152
Your car is kind of mangled.
It ended up on the front lawn.

1176
01:17:38,286 --> 01:17:42,689
We don't care about that, but why...
Why did he do it?

1177
01:17:46,561 --> 01:17:49,121
SALLY: Can the children go see
their brother Javier Solarte?

1178
01:17:49,197 --> 01:17:50,960
NURSE: Sure, just for a few minutes.
He's right here.

1179
01:17:51,366 --> 01:17:53,926
Go ahead, kids. So, Christine...

1180
01:17:55,937 --> 01:17:56,961
JORDAN: Are you okay?

1181
01:17:57,039 --> 01:17:58,768
KALEB: Are you okay?
JORDAN: What happened?

1182
01:17:59,007 --> 01:18:00,668
There was a message on your phone.

1183
01:18:01,410 --> 01:18:03,674
He found out you're going to
send them all away to another family.

1184
01:18:04,813 --> 01:18:08,010
And... Well...

1185
01:18:09,184 --> 01:18:10,981
-Come on, it's okay.
-Just tell us, it's all right.

1186
01:18:11,520 --> 01:18:14,045
He... He thought
you cared more about him than that.

1187
01:18:15,223 --> 01:18:16,520
DOROTHY: Mr. and Mrs. Danville.

1188
01:18:18,627 --> 01:18:20,060
-SALLY: Hi.
-Is Javier all right?

1189
01:18:20,228 --> 01:18:21,786
-Yeah, he's going to be fine.
-He's going to be okay.

1190
01:18:21,863 --> 01:18:25,458
-Oh. Thank goodness.
-Did you leave us a message?

1191
01:18:25,667 --> 01:18:27,134
Yeah, you didn't get it?

1192
01:18:27,869 --> 01:18:30,770
We found the perfect family.
They'll take all four.

1193
01:18:30,839 --> 01:18:32,363
Transition is set for this weekend.

1194
01:18:32,474 --> 01:18:35,568
No, we didn't get it, but Javier did.

1195
01:18:39,881 --> 01:18:41,348
Oh, I see.

1196
01:18:41,883 --> 01:18:46,843
Dorothy, we are happy to tell you
we don't need a transition.

1197
01:18:47,723 --> 01:18:51,489
We want to adopt the kids
and make it official.

1198
01:18:51,560 --> 01:18:55,257
DOROTHY: Oh, that's impossible now.
JASON: Why is that impossible?

1199
01:18:55,497 --> 01:18:58,523
Yeah, I mean, you begged us
to take these kids and now we want to.

1200
01:18:58,600 --> 01:19:00,830
-We're ready.
-That was before.

1201
01:19:01,369 --> 01:19:02,461
Before what?

1202
01:19:02,537 --> 01:19:05,529
I explained all of this to you
after the first incident.

1203
01:19:05,607 --> 01:19:07,939
I warned you. I was serious, I meant it.

1204
01:19:08,043 --> 01:19:10,568
Look, Javier, he was just upset
and he didn't know...

1205
01:19:10,645 --> 01:19:12,670
DOROTHY:
Mrs. Danville, we cannot allow it.

1206
01:19:13,081 --> 01:19:14,639
-Allow what?
-Yeah, I mean...

1207
01:19:15,717 --> 01:19:19,016
We've become a family now.
We love these children.

1208
01:19:19,087 --> 01:19:21,055
We want to make it official.

1209
01:19:21,189 --> 01:19:22,816
That is not the issue.

1210
01:19:22,891 --> 01:19:25,883
Family Services cannot take a risk,
and you two are a risk.

1211
01:19:26,261 --> 01:19:27,250
No, we're not.

1212
01:19:27,329 --> 01:19:29,661
JASON: Oh, come on, nobody starts out
being a perfect parent.

1213
01:19:29,731 --> 01:19:31,130
You need practice, you make mistakes,

1214
01:19:31,199 --> 01:19:33,690
and then, you know, sometimes you blow it...

1215
01:19:33,835 --> 01:19:36,133
Yes, and both of you have done all of that.

1216
01:19:36,204 --> 01:19:39,332
Now, I can't agree with your proposal,
and if you attempt it,

1217
01:19:39,407 --> 01:19:41,466
I'll have to fight you in a court of law.

1218
01:19:41,610 --> 01:19:45,410
Look, Dorothy, listen.
You know, when we all started with this,

1219
01:19:45,480 --> 01:19:49,917
we were just concerned
about the inconvenience in our lives,

1220
01:19:49,985 --> 01:19:54,027
about our careers and our relationship,
but these kids,

1221
01:19:54,923 --> 01:19:58,484
they changed everything and just set us
on a completely different path.

1222
01:19:58,560 --> 01:20:01,085
Better path, you know,
beyond our narrow vision.

1223
01:20:01,163 --> 01:20:03,859
Yeah,
we're ready just to give it all away

1224
01:20:03,932 --> 01:20:06,799
instead of taking it for ourselves,
and we mean that.

1225
01:20:08,069 --> 01:20:10,037
All good feelings aside,

1226
01:20:10,772 --> 01:20:14,433
there's no evidence that you two can
deal with this enormous responsibility.

1227
01:20:14,528 --> 01:20:15,528
We can.

1228
01:20:15,628 --> 01:20:17,607
Now all four children are to be remanded

1229
01:20:17,608 --> 01:20:20,073
into Family Services protective custody

1230
01:20:20,148 --> 01:20:22,207
-pending placement.
-You can't do this.

1231
01:20:22,284 --> 01:20:23,573
Excuse me.

1232
01:20:24,553 --> 01:20:25,611
Hello, Jordan.

1233
01:20:26,221 --> 01:20:28,246
My mother and father taught me
to speak my mind.

1234
01:20:29,658 --> 01:20:31,819
Yes, that's a good thing.

1235
01:20:32,494 --> 01:20:34,724
You think you know
the right thing to do, but you don't.

1236
01:20:35,463 --> 01:20:38,432
You have no idea how hard
Sally and Jason have tried

1237
01:20:38,500 --> 01:20:39,831
to be good parents.

1238
01:20:40,769 --> 01:20:43,431
It was an obligation at first,
we could tell that.

1239
01:20:45,774 --> 01:20:47,639
But it's different now.

1240
01:20:48,410 --> 01:20:51,402
Javier didn't do what he did
because they were bad parents,

1241
01:20:51,479 --> 01:20:54,880
he did it because he was...
He loved them.

1242
01:20:54,950 --> 01:20:57,214
And he was upset because
he thought that they didn't love him.

1243
01:20:59,254 --> 01:21:00,778
But we all know that's not true.

1244
01:21:03,291 --> 01:21:04,553
And we all love them.

1245
01:21:06,261 --> 01:21:09,628
And we won't live with anyone else no
matter what you intend to do in court.

1246
01:21:11,666 --> 01:21:14,794
-I appreciate your feelings, honey, but...
-Wait, wait, wait.

1247
01:21:17,005 --> 01:21:19,974
There's a reason Sally was on that list.

1248
01:21:21,543 --> 01:21:23,977
My mother believed in her,

1249
01:21:24,045 --> 01:21:26,809
trusted her with her most sacred possessions.

1250
01:21:27,148 --> 01:21:30,879
Out of respect for that,
for my mother and father,

1251
01:21:30,952 --> 01:21:34,080
will you please reconsider
and not fight against it?

1252
01:21:47,168 --> 01:21:51,161
Can you appreciate how sincerely
our department considers

1253
01:21:51,239 --> 01:21:53,901
the welfare of children, because
nothing else really matters, you know.

1254
01:21:54,342 --> 01:21:56,139
-Look, Dorothy, I...
-I listened to Jordan.

1255
01:21:58,880 --> 01:22:02,475
I feel the looks on these faces,
and there's no question.

1256
01:22:03,952 --> 01:22:06,352
The welfare of these children

1257
01:22:09,524 --> 01:22:12,015
could never be placed
in more capable or loving hands.

1258
01:22:13,094 --> 01:22:14,118
Your case is closed.

1259
01:22:15,630 --> 01:22:17,928
-Really?
-Oh. Thank you, thank you!

1260
01:22:17,999 --> 01:22:19,023
SALLY: Oh, yay!

1261
01:22:19,100 --> 01:22:20,931
-Come here.
-Oh, my God.

1262
01:22:21,002 --> 01:22:24,403
JAVIER: I'm sorry about the car, man.
JASON: Don't worry about the car, pal.

1263
01:22:24,606 --> 01:22:25,698
SALLY: You okay?

1264
01:22:32,847 --> 01:22:34,644
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1265
01:22:39,688 --> 01:22:43,146
I'm telling you what,
these dancers from China were awesome.

1266
01:22:43,224 --> 01:22:45,556
All right, so listen.
I'm seeing a lot of familiar faces.

1267
01:22:45,627 --> 01:22:47,686
You're here every year,
I'm here every year,

1268
01:22:47,762 --> 01:22:51,254
we all come for the same reason,
to celebrate the family of man, right?

1269
01:22:51,333 --> 01:22:52,857
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

1270
01:22:52,934 --> 01:22:55,334
This festival is definitely
near and dear to my heart,

1271
01:22:55,403 --> 01:22:58,167
and I tell you what,
we have a girl that is a late entry,

1272
01:22:58,239 --> 01:23:01,003
but she is definitely someone
I'm sure you're gonna love.

1273
01:23:01,276 --> 01:23:03,176
Ladies and gentlemen,
put your hands together

1274
01:23:03,244 --> 01:23:06,179
for Sally Danville and Plane Truth.

1275
01:23:06,247 --> 01:23:08,306
(ALL CHEERING)

1276
01:23:16,958 --> 01:23:19,358
Thank you so much,
it's so great to be here.

1277
01:23:19,427 --> 01:23:22,692
I just want to thank Randy Jackson,
I want to thank my manager Klay,

1278
01:23:23,631 --> 01:23:27,158
but I really just want to thank
my husband Jason.

1279
01:23:27,302 --> 01:23:31,602
And this next song, it's brand new
and I wrote it for my family.

1280
01:23:31,806 --> 01:23:33,296
(LAUGHS)

1281
01:23:33,908 --> 01:23:35,808
Wow, my family, so...

1282
01:23:39,714 --> 01:23:41,648
Here we go, I hope you like it.

